				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sony has repeatedly said for many <span style="color: red"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">years</span></span> that the mage root is our <span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">pet</span>.
<br />

<br />
This is why we have never gotten root and this is also why there are continued and overwhelming number of complaints that our pets do not do what they are supposed to do (mage only defense remember?) and had always done pre-PoP expansion.  They were helped this year with a modest improvement in their mitigation ability, but only if you have high end focus do they really show this improvement.
<br />

<br />
After 2 years of lies by Sony in promising to fix an obviously broken problem, I have no faith they will actually fix the problem in any fashion that will affect the 99% of the mage population that is without the highest end pet foci in the game.
<br />

<br />
It is quite possible that with the continued boosting of dmg output by mobs to make it harder and harder for the higher geared folks, there is no way to truly balance the mage class. It is possible to break something so badly and for so long that it becomes impossible to fix it. The very game mechanics are probably the imbalancing problem for all the classes in EQ now.
<br />

<br />
- Talron da Magus on Bertox</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
